The paper deals with sparsification of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The methods proposed in the paper are model-independent and do not require retraining, which suggests that they may be applicable to a wide range of CNN architectures and applications, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the computational demands of CNNs, which could be relevant to distributed, parallel, and high-performance computing (cs.DC).
